<!--311-->Uruk Lieutenant x4    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This Might look like a weird deck to play at the beginning, but once I played it a couple of times I found out that it counters A Lot of decks. For the Free People side,  Nazgul I got 2 Flaming Brands and Trust should be enough for any Nazgul to handle.  Against Uruk hai as soon as I get gandalf and aragorn out I will kill off merry as soon as possible to stay at 4 companions and stay away from their savergry&#39;s.  Then the Trusting begins.  Saroun is weak enough that I dont have to worry but I have Deep in Thought to get rid of their conditions.  Moria i should be able to handle with Bounder and Trust it will be hard to overwhelm frodo and I have Deep in Thought to get rid of any swarms.<br />
<br />
Now for the Shadow side.  It looks really strange but it really works, the moria is for the swarm ability and to add shadow for my big Uruk Hai.  The tower assassins are for the mirrorand any pesky allies that are hurting me.  They are comming is to cycle through my deck quicker and to get more free people things in my hand.<br />
<br />
<br />
Thats about it, if I missed anything, D-Mail me and I&#39;ll answer any questions. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
